Condolences and goodwill messages continue to pour after the demise of veteran journalist and columnist Philip Ochieng who died on Tuesday evening aged 82. according to the family, Ochieng who had been ailing for some time succumbed to pneumonia and other complications associated with old age. ODM party leader Raila Odinga described the late Ochieng&rsquo; as a &lsquo;veteran journalist and legendary columnist with an unmatched prowess of the English language. our senior political reporter patrick amimo looks into the life and times of Ochieng.